1 - install mongodb community server
! assign a windows service to mongodb start
! create the environment

https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-windows/#manually-create-a-windows-service-for-mongodb-community-edition

2- install mongodb compass

3- maven dependencies:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.mongodb</groupId>
    <artifactId>mongo-java-driver</artifactId>
    <version>3.6.3</version>
</dependency>

4- http://mongodb.github.io/mongo-java-driver/3.4/driver/tutorials/perform-write-operations/

5- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=khLaOfy6BCE

optional - Mongo odm https://www.infoq.com/articles/mongodb-java-orm-bcd

6- Using Morphia
http://mongodb.github.io/morphia/1.3/guides/annotations/#embedded
http://www.thejavageek.com/2015/08/24/save-entity-using-morphia/

<dependency>
            <groupId>org.mongodb.morphia</groupId>
            <artifactId>morphia</artifactId>
            <version>1.3.2</version>
        </dependency>

7- Using unique index for names:
https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/core/index-unique/

8- Morphia @Annotations.